The Lagos High Court in Ikeja has ordered the Nigerian Navy to pay the entitlement and ben­efits of the retired late Rear Admiral Ndubuisi Kanu, a for­mer Military Administrator of Lagos, to an interest-yielding dedicated account. Justice Christopher Ba­logun made the order in an ongoing proceeding of a suit filed by Chief Mrs. Gladys Ndubuisi Kanu on Monday against her stepchildren and Nigerian Navy over his estate. In the suit marked LD/3685FPM/2021, Chief Mrs. Gladys is seeking to be declared as the only legal wife of the late Admiral Kanu. NiMET Warns Of Extreme Heats As Temperature Rises Across States Yobe Commends AFRYDEV For Training GBV Survivors The respondents in the suit are children of the de­ceased, Kelly Kanu, Nigerian Navy, Simone Abiona (Nee Kanu), Andrey Joe-Ezigbo (nee Kanu), Paula Kanu and Karen Johnson (Nee Kanu), Jeffery Kanu, Laura Kanu, Stephen Kanu and Josephine Ndubuisi Kanu. Chief Gladys also sought for an order of the court to de­clare that she is the only wid­ow of the late Admiral Kanu.